STRICT_DECIMAL

public static final Pattern STRICT_DECIMAL
A Pattern object that matches a decimal number that has at least one digit before the decimal point. The decimal point and the numbers to the right are optional.

0, 11., 2.3 are all good candidates. While .1, . are not.

Method Detail

nullable

public static Pattern nullable(Pattern pattern)
Modifies given pattern to empty string Pattern if it can match empty string.

nullable Pattern is a simplification of an input Pattern that may be convenient when using derivatives. If the pattern matches the empty string, then the nullable pattern will match the empty string, otherwise it will match NEVER.

Parameters:
pattern - nested pattern to make nullable.
Returns:
a Pattern that's a nullable version of given pattern.
